Spray the inside of a 4-quart slow cooker with the cooking spray. Place the chicken into the cooker. Place 1 tablespoon of butter onto each chicken breast half. Stir the onion soup mix, mushroom soup, milk and rice in a medium bowl. Pour over the chicken. Sprinkle with the cheese. Cover and cook on LOW for 8 to 9 hours* or until the chicken is cooked through.